        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-03-24T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-03-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="128"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                <head>128. Telegram From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD3" type="from"
                        >Rusk</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d128fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_KJF2"
                            >Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files, Vietnam, Country
                        Series 3/1/62-3/12/62. Secret; Priority; Eyes Only; Limit
                        Distribution.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-03-24T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1962—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 100. For Acting Secretary from
                    Secretary. Reference your recent report strange aircraft over South Vietnam<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d128fn2">See <ref target="#d120">Document 120</ref>.</note> I
                    believe it of utmost importance that we not permit other side to establish
                    precedent of air supply, reconnaissance or other chores on behalf of Vietcong.
                    We must not let them repeat Xieng Khouang maneuver in South Vietnam. Hope
                    arrangements are being made to see that hostile aircraft over South Vietnam are
                    shot down.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
